# Task 6

## Objective
1. Rename files from Day1–Day5 to Task1–Task5
2. Create an AWS account
3. Enable Multi-Factor Authentication (MFA)
4. Create Task6 documentation file
5. Stage, commit, and push all changes to GitHub

---
                 SOLUTION:
 
# Part 1: Renaming Files

### Step 1: I Navigated to my Project Directory
cd /mnt/c/users/hp/onedrive/desktop/linux

### Step 2: I Renamed the  Files Using Git
git mv Day1 Task1
git mv Day2 Task2
git mv Day3 Task3
git mv Day4 Task4
git mv Day5 Task5

### Step 3: I Confirmed the  Changes
git status

---

## Part 2: Creating AWS Account

1. Visited https://aws.amazon.com/
2. Clicked on “Create an AWS Account”
3. Entered email and account name
4. Created root user password
5. Verified email address
6. Entered billing information
7. Completed phone verification
8. Selected Basic Support Plan (Free Tier)

---

## Part 3: Enabling MFA

1. I Logged into AWS Management Console
2. Navigated to Security Credentials
3. Selected Multi-Factor Authentication (MFA)
4. Chose Virtual MFA Device
5. Installed an authenticator app on phone (Google Authenticator)
6. Scanned the QR code
7. Entered two generated codes to activate MFA

---

## Part 4: Creating Task6 File

### Step 1: I Created the File With The Command Below
